      "side": 1,
      "message": "[warning] Line 49: The `scheme` field is free-form with no validation anywhere in the patch. A malicious or misconfigured client could set it to an arbitrary string (e.g. `javascript`, `file`, `data`) which a UI might naïvely use in URI construction, leading to scheme-injection. Add validation in `mapToServiceRecord` (and/or `fromJson`) to reject or sanitize values that are not in a small allow-list (e.g. `\"\"`, `\"http\"`, `\"https\"`).",
      "revId": "58983fc435da4a5cad9983e2c0b931428819f20e",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
