      "side": 1,
      "message": "[warning] Line 52: Adding `scheme` to the MSGPACK_DEFINE_MAP is a wire-protocol breaking change for older peers. A v1 peer that deserializes a v2 message with the extra field may reject or misparse it (depending on msgpack configuration). Consider: (1) bumping the protocol version constant so peers can negotiate, or (2) using MSGPACK_DEFINE_MAP with optional/defaulted handling so that the field is silently ignored by older decoders. At minimum, document the backward-compatibility story.",
      "revId": "58983fc435da4a5cad9983e2c0b931428819f20e",
